writes:

<< What the heck is a CVS? I remember the beans from a hundred years ago
when I
was a kid. They were great, but I don't know what a CVS is to go buy them,
and the bean site says they are out till July! Help! LOL

Teresa >>

Teresa

I went to the web site too and on one of the pages they explained that in
February or March the little caterpillar inside becomes a moth, bores a hole
in the bean pod and "hatches" out. So any beans you get now are probably
close to hatching. I made note of the web site and will order some a bit
later and wait until July to have them delivered. I'm just hoping enough of
them stay alive to actually hatch so the kids can see that happen.

Kris
